From Mike Harpe Subject Re How to drive an array of LEDs Phil Torre writes I have a project in mind that requires an array of LEDs that can be addressed individually by a microprocessor say or so Is there an LSI that is designed to drive an LED array including RAM to hold the array state or failing that some way of multiplexing the display so I don't have to latch a bit for each LED using a discrete latch I want to avoid having a huge board covered with if possible Thanks in Maxim makes a chip that does exactly what you The drives segment LED displays with full decode or drives discrete LED's with a wire serial The chips can also be cascaded to allow very large I am working on a sign display using this I'll have to post the contact info for Maxim later it's at There was a series of articles on this chip in the last couple of Circuit Cellar Ink' Mike Harpe Michael Harpe Programmer Analyst Information Technology Ormsby University of Louisville Louisville He's not a man he's a remorseless eating machine The Simpsons